article.headline: Delaware 75, Old Dominion 67
article.story: NEWARK, Del. -- Jawan Carter had 29 points, including seven free throws in the final 51 seconds, as Delaware held off Old Dominion 75-67 on Saturday night in the Colonial Athletic Association opener for both teams. The Blue Hens (3-2), who won three straight games for the first time since Dec. 21, 2008, snapped the Monarchs' five-game winning streak. Delaware led by as many as 11 points in the second half, then Old Dominion (5-2), the defending league champion and preseason favorite, cut the lead to 56-54 with 5:24 left. The Blue Hens pulled away with an 8-1 run. Holding a 66-61 lead, Delaware hit 9 of 10 free throws in the last 51 seconds. Carter, who posted his third straight 20-point effort, made all 12 of his field goal attempts from beyond the arc, hitting 6. He also made 11 of 15 free throws. Frank Hassell had 19 points to lead the Monarchs and Kent Bazemore had 17.
